  "unit": {
    "verdict": "ok",
    "note": "Past perfect (had + past participle; an action completed before another past action; with already/just/by the time/after/before; past-perfect-vs-past-simple sequencing; error classes: had+base, wrong participle, tense choice). 46 vocab + 82 grammar, full v1 parity (floor 40 → 82 items / 11 formats — largest unit in the wave). 4 verify lenses clean after fixes: reworded 11 'Past perfect' + 1 'Verb' prompts → 'had + die 3. Form' / '2. Form' (MORE! form-numbering, jargon-free); reframed mc.005 to require the earlier-action sequence (was ambiguous — both past simple and past perfect were grammatical); granted the past-participle / irregular-past load + crime carriers (burglars/party/wallet/film + ~75 grants); stripped 18 cross-item-redundant glosses; relabeled richtig/falsch group-sorts → ✓/✗; reworded 'Grundform'→'einfachen Form'; pipe-joined mc.004's 2-blank combinations; dropped a lemma-clashing distractorPool entry (keep-an-eye-on); fixed retire's enToDe with an umlaut-bearing variant ('mit der Arbeit aufhören' — V-10 needs ≥1 DE-stop or umlaut, retire's 'in Pension/Rente gehen' had neither). The 4 gloss audits (chest→heart, test, recognise) are correct; 52 translation audits accurate. 3 defensible warns: criminal 'Verbrecher/in' + get-hold-of 'an etwas gelangen' (homograph heuristic), one sentence-initial 'Sie' in explainDe (=she/they). mc.007/mc.014 left as defensible (past-simple distractors are grammatical but mitigated by the explicit 'frühere Handlung' framing). Validate green."
